Description: This is an Ibanez RT450 in Tobacco Sunburst. Condition is very good considering its 26 year age. These were only made for one production year. It has the usual wear from playing but very slight. The body is very clean, with only one small dent near the bridge as seen in the photo. The back of the body is clean but with a faint amount of buckle rash. I had to turn the body into the glare from the window to get it to show up on the photos. The neck is super clean and comfortable with the Viper profile. Other than the Petrucci models from the early-mid 90's, I believe this was the only other model with this profile? At any rate, this is an all-around workhorse of a guitar with it's flexible pickup configuration AND coil splitting. It was always babied here at my home. It's been in my personal collection for approximately 10 years. Besides playing occasionally at home, it might have been used in a church setting for a handful of sets, but other than that it has been stored in my smoke free home. This will probably be the one that "got away" in a few years time. Honestly, just need to make a little more room in the closet. The pickguard was created by RedZline many years ago. They used the original pickguard as the pattern so it's basically a one-off. It's a nice 3-ply pearl white pickguard that works well with the black pickups and knobs...I was going for an "Andy Timmons vibe", BUT the original tortoise plate is included! The 1992 catalog image in the last photo is just for reference. I've tried to represent everything within the 12 photo limit, but if you have any other requests for photos I would be very happy to send more. It will be carefully shipped via UPS Ground method.
